modules.description: Provides functions to pretty-print lists, arrays, and hashtables with customizable prefix strings and float precision settings. Works with standard OCaml data structures including lists, arrays, and hash tables. Enables concise visualization of complex data during debugging by formatting values with specified decimal precision.

The module offers formatted printing and pretty-printing operations for structured data, including lists, arrays, tuples, and hash tables with diverse key-value types like integers, strings, and floats. It handles nested structures with consistent bracketing, semicolon separation, and customizable prefixes, while supporting precision settings for numeric values. Use cases include debugging complex data hierarchies, generating human-readable logs, and visualizing hash table contents in applications requiring structured output.
